The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has forecasted a possible rise in temperature in some states across the country. In a weather alert issued by the Central Forecast Office (CFO) on Sunday and made available to journalists in a statement signed by Muntari Yusuf Ibrahim, General Man­ager, Public Relations Unit, NiMET noted that the areas expected to record tempera­ture greater than 35°C and less than 40°C include parts of Niger, Kwara, FCT, Kogi, Benue, Nasarawa and Taraba. According to the state­ment, the entire inland states of the South (excluding Enu­gu) and most parts of the coastal states (excluding La­gos) are expected to be in the same temperature range. Yobe Commends AFRYDEV For Training GBV Survivors 2023: Northern Presidency Beyond Buhari Will Be Security Risk –… The two-day forecast, how­ever, observed that on Febru­ary 1, places in the South that are expected to be in the same temperature range include parts of Oyo, Ogun, Osun, Ondo, Edo, Delta, Enugu, Riv­ers, Abia, Akwa Ibom, Ebonyi and Cross River.